==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: hipped
<hw>hipped</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>having hips; or, having
hips of a specified type; -- used in combination; <as>as,
wide-<ex>hipped</ex></as>.</def> <wns>[wns=1]</wns>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Architecture)</fld> <def>peaked and having sloping
ends rather than gables; -- of roofs; <as>as, a <ex>hipped</ex> roof has
sloping ends rather than gables</as>.</def> <wns>[wns=2]</wns>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> hip-roofed.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>hippie</ent>⟦br⟧
